author: dos
msg: handle zero-length messages when not in --cs_paths_only mode; we send a blank message rather than skipping the message so that the result output is identical to the output if the client was running in --cs_paths_only; in any case, people should remove zero-length messages from their corpora (there's no way to receive a headerless message without an error in your mail system) and fix their procmail maildir config that is quite likely broken
